#Text=Vintage plane crashes into road during Shoreham Airshow in England
#Text=Sunday , August 23 , 2015
#Text=The crashed aircraft , pictured in 2013 during a display .
#Text=Image : Alan Wilson .
#Text=Police warn more bodies may remain to be found after yesterday 's crash of a vintage jet killed at least seven people .
#Text=The Hawker Hunter crashed into a busy road during the Shoreham Airshow in England .
#Text=The plane failed to pull out of a large loop at around 1:20p . m.
#Text=It hit the nearby A27 road , erupting into a fireball and leaving cars burned out and heavily damaged .
#Text=The scene in West Sussex is near the town of Shoreham .
#Text=Pilot Andy Hill is presently alive but critically injured in hospital .
#Text=He has previously flown with British Airways and the Royal Air Force .
#Text=Two of the dead are Worthing United FC football players , Matthew Grimstone and Jacob Schilt , who were on their way to a match .
#Text=Also killed was Matt Jones , 24 , who worked as a personal trainer .
#Text=He came from Littlehampton and was giving a friend a lift .
#Text=A vintage Daimler wedding limousine on its way to collect a bride was also caught up in the crash , but its owner Chariot Chauffeurs say they are unclear on if the driver was a fatality .
#Text=Sussex Police and the Air Accidents Investigation Branch are investigating .
#Text=Police Superintendent Jane Derrick said last night , " At this time we are continuing to search[ ... ]

#Text=Assistant Chief Constable Steve Barry today said eleven people are  highly likely to have died in this tragedy " , based upon " our initial work at the site " and " inquiries following calls to the emergency services from worried families and friends " .

column1: #Text=He said officers currently remain at the " incredibly large " scene .
#Text=There are plans to remove plane wreckage using a crane tomorrow .
#Text=The pilot , Hill , was experienced , with years of display flying under his belt and a military career that included flying Harrier jump-jets .
#Text=David Wildridge , another pilot who took part yesterday , said Hill is " well-known and well-loved " , " very professional " , and that his Harrier experience made him " the best of the best .
